# SHA-256 checksums for Bitcoin and Electrum binaries
# Verify with: shasum -a 256 -c macos/checksums.sha256
# Generated with: shasum -a 256 <files> > macos/checksums.sha256
# Format: <sha256>  <path>  version=<semver>
# Note: macOS app bundles may change hash after codesign or quarantine changes.
# Integrity/rollback only, NOT authenticity: entries are recorded by the updater
# after a PGP-verified download. They detect later corruption/tampering of an
# installed binary; they do NOT by themselves prove a binary is a genuine
# release (that is the PGP signature step's job).

